column4: Diversity (Understanding Race, Ethnicity, and Gender) – DIVU2 Analyze constructs – Students will explain ways in which race, ethnicity, and/or gender are culturally and socially constructed.
column11: Advanced: Demonstrate a sophisticated and multi-layered ability to explain ways in which race, ethnicity, and/ or gender are culturally and socially constructed.
column13: Proficient: Demonstrate an advanced ability to explain ways in which race, ethnicity, and/or gender are culturally and socially constructed.
column15: Progressing: Demonstrate a basic ability to explain ways in  which race, ethnicity, and/or gender are culturally  and socially constructed.
column17: Beginning: Demonstrate a partial ability to explain ways in which race, ethnicity, and/or gender are culturally and socially constructed.
column19: Unsatisfactory: Demonstrates little ability to explain ways in which race, ethnicity, and/or gender are culturally and socially constructed.
